\f0\i [Jumps up.]
\f1\i0  My goodness, it\'92s delightful to think of, Christine! Free from care! To be able to be free from care, quite free from care; to be able to play and romp with the children; to be able to keep the house beautifully and have everything just as Torvald likes it! And, think of it, soon the spring will come and the big blue sky! Perhaps we shall be able to take a little trip\'97perhaps I shall see the sea again! Oh, it\'92s a wonderful thing to be alive and be happy. 
\f0\i [A bell is heard in the hall.]
\f1\i0 \
